text: I have never personally patronised O'ven Bakery, but from my point of view it is nothing more than a hawker stall. Not much of its wares are ever displayed, although, from the menu, which photos I have shot, indicated quite a spread that I have never seen. Nevertheless, I have seen others who come regularly, and from what I heard their delicacies are actually good.
To me price doesn't justify the quality reason being ,paying huge percentage to landlord while savings can only derived from  quality of products in most cases .
Gillman's Seafood is now here. Same good standards of it's original.
Wanna explore the coolest seasons on town well its here
Spacious sitting, comfortable for evening  dining.
